  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail and chop the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cut the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>into quarters, keeping the skin on</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> Cumberland sausages </strong>to one side of an <strong>oiled</strong> baking tray</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong> and <strong>onion quarters </strong>to the other side and scatter with the <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20 min or until the sausages and vegetables are starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the<strong> parsley</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Zest 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>lemon zest</strong> and <strong>capers</strong> together as finely as you can and transfer to a small bowl</p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>gremolata dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>wheat berries</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook over a high heat for 12-15 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and leave to cool</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausages and vegetables have started to brown, add the <strong>baby plum tomatoes</strong> to the tray</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 10 min further until the tomatoes have started to burst and the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1118.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a low heat</p><p>Once warm, add the<strong> chilli jam</strong> and the juice of the remaining<strong> lemon</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce is thick and sticky</p><p>Once cooked, add the <strong>sausages</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the sausages are fully coated in the sauce</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
